But even Supreme Court Justice Antonin Scalia, writing for the majority in the Heller case that stripped D.C. of its handgun ban, stated conclusively: ‘Nothing in our opinion should be taken to cast doubt on longstanding prohibitions on the possession of firearms by felons and the mentally ill, or laws forbidding the carrying of firearms in sensitive places such as schools and government buildings.’”[/b]I don’t see how a National Park can be included in the definition of “sensitive places.” National Parks are frequented by the same people who are in your neighborhood, that walk next to you on our streets.
